# ORBIT Repo & Deployment Policy

## ✅ WRITE — Active projects (create, edit, deploy here)
- **REBUS-ORBIT GitHub org** — all repos (`orbit-server`, `orbit-infra`, `orbit-sdk`, `orbit-connectors`, `prism`)
- **VM 211** (`10.0.200.211`) — ORBIT production (runs ORBIT + PRISM)
- **PRISM** container on VM 211

## 🚫 READ ONLY — Never modify, commit to, or deploy from
- `CheekiSkrub/*` GitHub repos (including `speckle-server-dev`, `REBUS-Speckle`, etc.)
- `/home/rebus/speckle-server-dev/` on any VM
- Speckle VMs: **VM 201** (`10.0.200.11`) and **VM 301** (`10.0.200.112`)
- Any `speckle-*` Docker images or containers on the old VMs

## Rule
When a task requires reading legacy Speckle source for reference (e.g. finding email template structure), that is acceptable — but **no commits, no pushes, no file edits** in those repos or VMs.

All new builds, deploys, and commits go to **REBUS-ORBIT** only.
